<h3 id="toc3"><span>what's this?</span></h3>
<p>Underread and Underrated is a project intended to shine a spotlight on, well, underread and underrated pages!</p>
<h3 id="toc4"><span>oh neat. What's the blurb for?</span></h3>
<p>As part of the associated UaU initiative, each month we'll be picking an element of SCP lore that people outside the general gestalt might not know about. We're also hosting writing challenges involving said lore!</p>
<h3 id="toc5"><span>may i suggest [blank] for the topic?</span></h3>
<p>Sure! Do note, however, that anything with a dedicated hub<sup class="footnoteref"><a id="footnoteref-1" href="javascript:;" class="footnoteref" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnote-1')">1</a></sup> above +100 in rating can't be made topic. Sorry! D:</p>
<p>Suggestions should be PM'd to <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/uraniumempire" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1613974); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1613974&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1609691963" alt="UraniumEmpire" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1613974)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/uraniumempire" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1613974); return false;">UraniumEmpire</a></span>!</p>
<h3 id="toc6"><span>oh cool how do i participate?</span></h3>
<p>Just PM <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/uraniumempire" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1613974); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1613974&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1609691963" alt="UraniumEmpire" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1613974)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/uraniumempire" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1613974); return false;">UraniumEmpire</a></span> a link to your piece and she'll post it on next month's &quot;Last Month's Pieces and Topic&quot; section!</p>
<p>For artists: try to link to whatever social media page is hosting the art. It saves us space and ensures we have a solid reference.</p>
